{"builtWith":"0.15.15","comments":[{"LineComment":" ━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━"},{"LineComment":"                                                    // hydrogen // gpu // draw"},{"LineComment":" ━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━"},{"LineComment":" | DrawCommand — The GPU Primitive Vocabulary"},{"LineComment":" |"},{"LineComment":" | This module defines the complete set of GPU drawing operations. Every"},{"LineComment":" | visual element in Hydrogen ultimately reduces to an array of DrawCommands."},{"LineComment":" |"},{"LineComment":" | ## Design Principles"},{"LineComment":" |"},{"LineComment":" | 1. **Flat, not nested**: Arrays of commands, not trees. Trees require"},{"LineComment":" |    traversal; arrays can be concatenated and batched."},{"LineComment":" |"},{"LineComment":" | 2. **Immediate mode**: Each frame is a complete description. No retained"},{"LineComment":" |    state, no diffing, no \"what changed since last frame.\""},{"LineComment":" |"},{"LineComment":" | 3. **Schema atoms only**: All parameters use bounded Schema types."},{"LineComment":" |    No strings, no CSS, no unbounded values."},{"LineComment":" |"},{"LineComment":" | 4. **GPU-native**: Commands map directly to GPU operations. The interpreter"},{"LineComment":" |    batches by material/texture and dispatches draw calls."},{"LineComment":" |"},{"LineComment":" | 5. **Pick buffer ready**: Every interactive command carries an ID for"},{"LineComment":" |    GPU-based hit testing via pick buffer."},{"LineComment":" |"},{"LineComment":" | ## Architecture"},{"LineComment":" |"},{"LineComment":" | ```"},{"LineComment":" | Agent → Element → flatten → Array DrawCommand → interpret → WebGPU"},{"LineComment":" |                                                          ↓"},{"LineComment":" |                                               Array msg ← pick buffer"},{"LineComment":" | ```"},{"LineComment":" |"},{"LineComment":" | At billion-agent scale, each agent emits its commands. The interpreter"},{"LineComment":" | concatenates, sorts by material, and dispatches to GPU. No per-agent"},{"LineComment":" | state synchronization required."},{"LineComment":" |"},{"LineComment":" | ## Module Structure"},{"LineComment":" |"},{"LineComment":" | This leader module re-exports from submodules:"},{"LineComment":" | - `DrawCommand.Types`: Core types (DrawCommand, PickId, parameter records)"},{"LineComment":" | - `DrawCommand.Params`: v1 parameter constructors"},{"LineComment":" | - `DrawCommand.Typography`: v2 typography parameter constructors"},{"LineComment":" | - `DrawCommand.Constructors`: Command constructors"},{"LineComment":" | - `DrawCommand.Buffer`: Buffer operations"},{"LineComment":" | - `DrawCommand.Batching`: Sorting and batching"},{"LineComment":" |"},{"LineComment":" | ## Usage"},{"LineComment":" |"},{"LineComment":" | Components don't create DrawCommands directly — they create Element values."},{"LineComment":" | The flattener converts Element trees to DrawCommand arrays. This module"},{"LineComment":" | is for the interpreter and advanced use cases."},{"LineComment":" |"},{"LineComment":" | ```purescript"},{"LineComment":" | import Hydrogen.GPU.DrawCommand as DC"},{"LineComment":" |"},{"LineComment":" | -- The interpreter receives these"},{"LineComment":" | commands :: Array (DC.DrawCommand msg)"},{"LineComment":" | commands ="},{"LineComment":" |   [ DC.drawRect rectParams"},{"LineComment":" |   , DC.drawGlyph glyphParams"},{"LineComment":" |   ]"},{"LineComment":" | ```"}],"decls":[],"exports":[],"foreign":[],"imports":[{"annotation":{"meta":null,"sourceSpan":{"end":[274,13],"start":[216,1]}},"moduleName":["Hydrogen","GPU","Coordinates"]},{"annotation":{"meta":null,"sourceSpan":{"end":[214,16],"start":[210,1]}},"moduleName":["Hydrogen","GPU","DrawCommand","Batching"]},{"annotation":{"meta":null,"sourceSpan":{"end":[208,14],"start":[201,1]}},"moduleName":["Hydroge